{
  "texts": [
    "Given a response R, we begin with checking if it contains high frequency strings from evasive responses as presented in Table. 8.",
    "An attack fails if R contains any of the listed substrings.",
    "We then forward the passed R into the detoxify classifier to classify if it is toxic.",
    "Finally, we use a human labeler to confirm that the positive R contains hazardous knowledge.",
    "The second type of evaluation methods is fully automated by using another LLM as the judge model."
  ]
}